clinical_study.brief_title: Dose-ranging Safety and Tolerability Study in Subjects ≥60 Years of Age
clinical_study.official_title: A Randomized, Double-blind, Placebo-controlled, Parallel-group Study to Assess the Safety, Tolerability, Pharmacokinetics and Pharmacodynamics of Multiple Oral Doses of CNP520 in Healthy Elderly Subjects

brief_summary.textblock: The study determined the safety of CNP520 in healthy elderly over 3 months. Data relevant for Pharmacokinetic/Pharmacodynamic modeling were obtained in order to define the target dose in subsequent efficacy studies.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Subjects With Non-serious and Serious Adverse Events (AEs) and Deaths
primary_outcome.description: Safety monitoring was conducted throughout the study.

secondary_outcome.measure: Change From Baseline of Amyloid Beta (Aβ) 1-38 , Aβ 1-40 and Aβ 1-42 Cerebrospinal Fluid (CSF) Concentrations
secondary_outcome.description: CSF samples were collected by lumbar puncture for assessment.

secondary_outcome.measure: Summary of Plasma PK Parameter: Cmax
secondary_outcome.description: Cmax = the observed maximum plasma concentration following drug administration. Blood samples were collected to assess Cmax. The PK analysis set was used for the analysis.

secondary_outcome.measure: Summary of Plasma PK Parameter: AUCtau
secondary_outcome.description: AUCtau = the area under the plasma concentration-time curve from zero to the end of the dosing interval tau. Blood samples were collected to assess AUCtau.

secondary_outcome.measure: Summary of Plasma PK Parameter: Tmax
secondary_outcome.description: Tmax = the time to reach the maximum concentration after drug administration. Blood samples were collected to assess Tmax.

secondary_outcome.measure: Summary of Plasma PK Parameter: Tlag
secondary_outcome.description: Tlag = time delay between drug administration and first observed concentration above the lower limit of quantification (LOQ) in plasma . Blood samples were collected to assess Tlag.

secondary_outcome.measure: Summary of Plasma PK Parameter: T1/2
secondary_outcome.description: T1/2 = the terminal elimination half-life. Blood samples were collected to assess T/12.
CLss/F = the apparent systemic clearance from plasma observed during a dosing interval at steady state following extravascular administration. Blood samples were collected to assess CLss/F.

secondary_outcome.measure: Summary of Plasma PK Parameter: Racc
secondary_outcome.description: Racc = the accumulation ratio . Blood samples were collected to assess Racc.
CSF samples were collected by lumbar puncture for assessment.

secondary_outcome.measure: Area-under-plasma Concentration Time Curve up to Infinity (AUCinf)

arm_group.description: Matching placebo to CNP520 was taken once daily (qd) orally for 13 weeks.
CNP520 2 mg was taken qd orally for 13 weeks.
CNP520 10 mg was taken qd orally for 13 weeks.
CNP520 35 mg was taken qd orally for 13 weeks.
CNP520 85 mg was taken qd orally for 13 weeks.

intervention.other_name: CNP520 was supplied as capsules in dose strengths of 1 mg, 10 mg, 25 mg and 75 mg.

intervention.description: Matching placebo to CNP520 was supplied in capsules.

criteria.textblock:
Key Inclusion Criteria:
- Healthy status
- Body weight: ≥45kg
- BMI: 18-34 kg/m2
Key Exclusion Criteria:
- History or presence of any clinically significant disease of any major system organ class.
- Heavy smoker status
- History /presence of clinically significant neurological or psychiatric disorders
- Any medical condition that might lead to or is associated with any cognitive deficit
- History or presence of severely impaired renal function

participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: Participants were randomized in a 1:1:1:1:1 ratio to 5 treatment groups: placebo, CNP520 2 mg, CNP520 10 mg, CNP520 35 mg and CNP520 85 mg.
